Class RouteFetcher

    • com.mapbox.services.android.navigation.v5.route.RouteFetcher

  • public class RouteFetcher
extends java.lang.Object
    This class can be used to fetch new routes given a Location origin and RouteOptions provided by a RouteProgress.

      • findRouteFromRouteProgress

        public void findRouteFromRouteProgress(android.content.Context context,
                                       android.location.Location location,
                                       RouteProgress routeProgress)
        Calculates a new DirectionsRoute given the current Location and RouteProgress along the route.

        Uses RouteOptions.coordinates() and RouteProgress.remainingWaypoints() to determine the amount of remaining waypoints there are along the given route.

        Parameters:
        location - current location of the device
        routeProgress - for remaining waypoints along the route
        Since:
        0.13.0
